description:
I Only Have Eyes For You! (4 pages)

Jean falls for her boss, a television executive who is constantly working with beautiful, glamorous women.

Third Finger, Left Hand (5 pages)

Newlywed Anne has difficulty coping with all the work required to support her husband in their small apartment.

Never Let Me Go!

Fran had loved Keith since they were kids, but Fran's friends keep suggesting that she should see other fellows before committing permanently to Keith. Reluctantly, she finally takes their advice and breaks a date with Keith to go out on a double date with Doris. Her relationship with Keith is shaken when Keith sees her in the arms of another man.

Gift for a Gal (2 pages, Text)

Thanks for the Memory (4 pages)

Billy keeps leaving jobs he is unhappy with and Sue complains about this to him. Alice overhears their conversation and when Billy leaves for a job interview, she tells Sue about a similar situation she was in twenty years ago.

Lovely to Look At! (5 pages)

Gail is a fashion editor and her world is filled with glamor and wealthy suitors, but no hint of love. Then she bumps into a man who works in the sports department downstairs.
name: Lovely to Look At; Third Finger, Left Hand!
The Boy With the Most Comic Book in America

description: Due to the popular demand of Archie Comics' fans everywhere, we're shining the spotlight on Riverdale brighter than ever before. Tales From Riverdale Digest highlights the amazing supporting cast that have entertained generations... from Reggie and Moose to Sabrina and Josie, and every teen in between! Not to mention the hilarious group of adults in Riverdale! Of course, Archie, Betty, Veronica and Jughead still make appearances, too. "Riverdale High Yearbook": Just what the title says... a "yearbook" full of all the fun and excitement the kids at Riverdale High have experienced this year! From class photos to reminiscences about activities and clubs, homecoming, sports, class trips and more, the "gang's all here," including the faculty! Filled with poignant insights and hilarious anecdotes, there's no better jumping-on point for new readers than this... and no better addition to a long-time reader's collection!

"Double Trouble": Archie has double-booked himself again: he's promised Betty he'd lend moral support as she pitches in the county championship; and he's promised Veronica he'll help out at Mrs. Lodge's charity carwash. Lucky for him the two events are a block away... and his friend Jughead is kind enough to lend him his skateboard!
name: Double Trouble

description: "Buddy Building": Determined never to get sand kicked in his face again, Dilton builds a muscle-bound, strong-as-ten men exoskeleton that makes him the big kahuna of Riverdale Beach!
name: Buddy Building

description: "Renaissance Mantle": Riverdale's resident rabble-rouser takes center stage in this all-new tale. The Renaissance Fair is back in town, and Reggie is upset that Archie has been chosen to play the knight in shining armor, while he's relegating to court jester! Reggie decides that if he's considered nothing more than a practical joker, then he'll be the best practical joker ever... but who will have the last laugh?
name: Ranaissance Mantle

description: "Monitor Scream!": The new school year has only just begun, and already Archie is in trouble. Assuming giving Archie some responsibility will help, Mr. Weatherbee makes him a hall monitor. However, the only things Archie is good at monitoring are Veronica and Reggie... and he uses his new authority to keep the latter from the former! Plus, Ginger Lopez must design a dress for a class project. But when Ginger gets teamed up with a sci-fi loving freshman, can she still make it out of this world? Find out in, "Fashion Emergency." Plus, Sabrina stories based on the popular animated cartoon series!

'Bye, Bye Bee': Can it be so? Is Mr. Weatherbee really leaving his post at Riverdale High? It appears so, and while his replacement, Mr. Bartlett introduces himself as a pal of a principal, it soon becomes apparent that he's piranha in disguise! With both students and faculty caught in the crossfire, there's nothing else to do but form an alliance to try to get Weatherbee back! 'Summer Spirits': When all the electrical machines in the school start operating by themselves, Mr. Flutesnoot is convinced the school has been haunted. It will take a man of science to solve this mystery, so get going, Dilton!

Story Titles

  • Bye Bye Bee!
  • Rare Scare
  • Veronica Lodge: Attorney of Love
  • Space Spoof
  • Purple Passion
  • Switch Witch
  • Star Flaws
  • You May Already Be a Halloweener!
  • Image Conscious!
  • It's in the Cards!
  • Model Muddle
  • Air-Foiled
  • The Abraca-Dabbler
  • Summer Spirits!

"Dilton's Double (or A Tale of Two Diltons)": Annoying disruptions like chores around the house are really getting in the way of Dilton's scientific experiments. That is, until Dilton's android double takes over those chores. The only problem is, Dilton's double wants to take over everything... including a date with lovely Alison Adams! Will Dilton ditch his double and finally learn to multi-task?

"Mixed-up Media": Mr. Dee, Riverdale High's librarian and media specialist, arranges for the students to borrow the local university's TV production facilities to create their own programming. Each student is responsible for a segment that interests them, art instruction for Chuck, cooking for Jughead, etc. With all the egos involved, and the complications they bring with them, will the live broadcast be the informative program it's meant to be... or the latest (unintentional) comedy smash? It's "reality TV" as only Riverdale can deliver! PLUS: Puzzles, games and your chance to "Find Your Name in Print!"
name: Mixed-Up Media

description: Hail, hail the gang's all here in this uproarious digest full of fun and excitement as only Riverdale High's teens can provide! Featuring new stories and classic tales, plus puzzles, games, and your chance to 'Find Your Name in Print!'
name: Treasure Quest

description: 'Double 'W' Vision!': There's a new girl in school with bangs dyed red, eccentric mix & match fashions, buttons galore, an interest in entomology... and a pet tarantula named Tara! Veronica decides to keep a cautious distance, while Betty embraces the notion of a quirky yet creative new friend. If Veronica thinks she's unusual now, just wait until the new girl reveals her most surprising secret of all! Bonus: Puzzles, games and your chance to 'Find Your Name in Print!'
Trivia: This issue features the first appearance of Ken Hale, the Gorilla-Man, member of the Agents of Atlas.

'Role Muddle': To a group of young freshman, Archie has it all: two girls fighting over him, lots of friends, the attention of the faculty... he's definitely the 'Big Man on Campus' in their naive eyes! Attempting to emulate their hero, each soon realizes that Archie's antics often end in detention... where they all end up, sitting beside him!
name: Role Muddle

description: 'Summer Champ': It's off to summer camp for Dilton Doiley, but at Camp Copernicus, hiking, fishing, and canoeing are replaced by computer programming, chemistry experiments, and robot building. When Archie comes for a visit, he tries to teach these gifted and talented geniuses about traditional camp experiences, but it's Archie who learns a thing or two from this innovative crew!

'The Malted Falcon': Return with us to the days of film noir, when every movie detective wore a fedora and shadows lurked in every corner! Pop Tate plans to kick off a classic movie night at the Choklit Shop with a new drink called 'The Malted Falcon,' but the recipe is stolen before showtime! It's up to Dilton Doiley, teen detective to solve this dark chocolate mystery!
name: The Missing Malted Falcon

description: 'The Big Break': An injury during a football game leaves Archie's entire arm in a cast, but Archie's bad break becomes a 'good break' for Betty, as she offers to help Archie with all the everyday tasks he can't perform with one arm. Of course, this leaves Veronica contemplating a few more breaks, as Betty is getting all the attention!
name: The Big Break

description: "Shock 'n Roll": The Archies are back, and determined to win the "American Icon" talent contest. Unfortunately, their rivals Ray and the Ray-vons are determined to stop them using any dirty tricks necessary. But could their scheme backfire and cause the Archies to unintentionally create a brand-new dance craze? Check out the musical mayhem for yourself! Plus, puzzles, games, and your chance to "Find Your Name in Print!"
name: Shock 'N' Roll!
